skos:Concept.skos:prefLabel: {"id": "49817f40-60d4-4c56-b6ee-3d05a180c3ce", "value": "Is one of the few remaining concrete ready-mix plants constructed between 1923 and 1965"}

{"id": "d5e3465c-128e-4c07-845d-b44abfc72edb", "value": "Often themetically unified through multiple iterations of similar objects, colors, or motif designs"}

{"id": "a8f924f1-48cd-45ef-b230-36d359762d0b", "value": "Located on the wall(s) of a highly visible, and often ordinary, building in a community"}
{"id": "564441fa-31e9-4a1c-9aad-8adbeaea6740", "value": "Includes streetscape plantings, boulevards, landscaped medians and plantings associated with a parcel or subdivision"}
{"id": "9a599ce0-d06c-4446-9587-b485ef45578b", "value": "Was constructed between 1900 and 1945 as a cold storage warehouse"}
{"id": "35104ebe-934c-4ed5-b5ad-622d6efc96fc", "value": "Is associated with a person who made important individual contributions to industrial growth and development"}

{"id": "42242e87-4ed6-40b4-b86d-6b2ebac5663e", "value": "Fox Film Corp., 10201 West Pico; Paramount , 5451 Marathon and 5555 Melrose; RKO, 780 North Gower; Warner Brothers, 5842 Sunset and 7200 Santa Monica; Columbia, 1438 N Gower; United Artists, 1041 N Formosa; Universal Studios,1000 Universal Center Dr."}
{"id": "1b091249-a063-48f3-a17c-e9494c66fdf0", "value": "Is an excellent example of Tiki/Polynesian architecture"}

{"id": "dbe0d679-c628-4d8b-9df7-6dddfbd44373", "value": "Is one of the two remaining nineteenth century schools in Los Angeles: Old Farmdale School (2839 N. Easter Ave) and Old Vernon Avenue School (450 N. Grand Ave)"}
{"id": "a5b68b6c-6913-495f-99f2-299dd5a5ed59", "value": "Support service must be proven to be significant within the entertainment industry"}

{"id": "3e029189-e4f2-4ef0-9225-cb0da311aca3", "value": "May also be significant under the Industrial Design and Engineering theme"}
{"id": "9c6a4fe5-4dd5-4780-99f5-b26fddad45a0", "value": "May support a combination of backlit plastic, incandescent bulbs, neon tubing, and/or fluorescent tubing"}

{"id": "288b71f1-68a8-44a5-b9dd-3237b8398cc5", "value": "Windows arranged in bands, often terminating at corners"}
{"id": "67a47483-0e55-4e15-bd4e-d8b26de7bcf0", "value": "Development may have had a broad influence on suburban planning and design in L.A."}
{"id": "74bcf246-6de1-44b8-bea6-bb688ed42e15", "value": "Overall retains cohesiveness as a planned multi-family development"}
{"id": "e23a7653-fba1-48c9-8ec0-032eecb0dabe", "value": "Associated architectural styles may include Beaux Arts, Neoclassicism"}
{"id": "1430c09b-d938-4382-80bb-6b0f475516b9", "value": "Is an excellent example of the Storybook style"}
{"id": "50a0b7a1-7c03-4641-a202-bed1bbca8bdc", "value": "Large screens of perforated cast stone, or metal or concrete grills over expanses of glass"}

{"id": "60a45bfd-500f-45ca-b4a8-819cdb0affce", "value": "Associated with ethnic/cultural history of Los Angeles"}
{"id": "74f5db3f-e6fb-4130-89c0-80059c36fda9", "value": "Located adjacent to, or in the proximity of, a motion picture studio"}

{"id": "23de308f-952a-4180-aded-abcc2530d688", "value": "Is one of the four identified Aircraft Manufacturers: Hughs Aircraft, Douglas Aircraft, Navy Lockheed Service Center, Davis-Douglas Airplance Co."}

{"id": "19bdb7af-6dea-46c1-b999-b190509bbf7a", "value": "Is an excellent example of landscape architecture in the Modern style and/or represents the work of a significant landscape architect or designer"}
{"id": "49f3d826-5450-4cee-8c06-22d788082809", "value": "Should retain integrity of Location, Design, and Materials from the period of significance"}

{"id": "90ca9467-777f-4ef7-ba3e-e25b1471f5a6", "value": "May include residences designed in Late Nineteenth Century and/or Period Revival styles; may combine the themes to best represent the neighborhood and overall period of significance"}

{"id": "04c1f303-bb45-42fb-aed8-876c4d6e9b1b", "value": "May include areas for passive recreation, such as picnic areas, park furniture, planters, water features, artificial lakes, walking trails and pathways"}

{"id": "d9ad0a09-44ee-43df-8529-ff089061b448", "value": "May include natural features such as rocks, palm trees and other plantings"}

{"id": "5318705d-d1ad-4be5-8dc7-e4d22fa97aad", "value": "May be designed by a noted architect or designer"}

{"id": "f87ba5e6-9c4d-47c3-b36c-3b090a177c10", "value": "Some materials on individual buildings may have been removed or altered"}
{"id": "a14828dd-2e2a-40a1-8cad-2543b737d2d1", "value": "May be associated with an individual important in Tujunga's ethnic or women's history"}
{"id": "6a3e30f6-5a61-467f-853e-975117a5aadb", "value": "Developers known for creating distinctive or innovative suburban design concepts may also be considered a \"master\" under Criterion C"}

{"id": "3c8c7f84-edb5-476c-849a-96092a3118df", "value": "Individual must be proven to have made an important contribution to the early settlement and development of San Pedro"}

{"id": "3e6b6875-f383-485a-a23a-633a1b834466", "value": "Open landscape with agricultural features that may include a farm house, farm land, orchard/grove, agricultural outbuildings and related features such as corrals, irrigation systems, standpipes, and tanks"}
{"id": "beefad45-0dfe-476c-9ca9-b1d6870d8588", "value": "Steeply pitched roofs with forward-slanting, front facing gables and sweeping or curved lines"}
{"id": "2e700fee-eb13-4294-b1e1-a1eab497bf69", "value": "Some elements of setting (particularly rails or spur alignments) may have been removed"}

{"id": "2117e3d8-7a03-4c76-93e4-3d4dffeb0520", "value": "Is one of the first ten public housing complexes constructed in the City of Los Angeles (Ramona Gardens, 2830 Lancaster Ave; Avalon Gardens, 701 E 88th Pl; Pueblo del Rio, 1801 E 53rd St; Hacienda Village (Gonzaque Village), 1515 E 105th St)"}
{"id": "e9afcede-b4a2-4074-ab23-469af73c8235", "value": "Collections of rare species or exotic species, such as palms, or ornamental specimen examples"}
{"id": "084cbc67-aa00-4dbd-895d-767259e3aec7", "value": "Associated architectural styles: WPA Moderne, Art Deco, Streamline Moderne, Spanish Colonial Revival, Classical Revival and International"}
{"id": "7affbbe8-0dc6-4b0f-a1ff-dbae626091cb", "value": "Represents an early or rare example of the style in the community in which it is located"}

{"id": "30dc0a49-6d0d-4906-b99d-3c695d59a584", "value": "May be used for a different tenant or industy than that for which is was originally developed"}

{"id": "5cf52772-3edb-44c7-a9ae-07ce58d2c9e6", "value": "Carved, inscribed, or attached to the building as an indication of ownership, business, or year of construction"}

{"id": "edce8be7-9b59-48c6-978f-1aefb609cc51", "value": "Displays eclectic and starkly contrasting elements, materials, colors, patterns, or massing, often resulting in a loosely- assembled or unfinished appearance"}
